"```sql\nSELECT \n    (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM Patient WHERE SEX = 'M' AND ID IN (SELECT ID FROM Laboratory WHERE UA <= 8.0)) AS Male_Count,\n    (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM Patient WHERE SEX = 'F' AND ID IN (SELECT ID FROM Laboratory WHERE UA <= 6.5)) AS Female_Count\n```\nThis SQL query counts the number of male patients with abnormal uric acid counts (UA <= 8.0) and the number of female patients with abnormal uric acid counts (UA <= 6.5). The results can be used to calculate the ratio of male to female patients."